<section class="manifesto" id="manifesto" tabindex="-1">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="display statement draw">
      Set, setting, and&nbsp;schema<span class="dot">.</span>
    </h2>

    {/* the buyer's moment, in second person — most people who need this
        work don't know it until someone names their situation */}
    <ul class="moments">
      <li>The biggest contract you’ve ever chased just landed, and nobody knows what the security policy should look like.</li>
      <li>You’re hiring clinicians but nobody is in charge of the data.</li>
      <li>An insurer just asked for your incident response plan. You don’t have one.</li>
      <li>Someone bolted an AI notetaker onto session notes and nobody read its terms.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="body">
      <p>
        Regulators are treating psychedelics as medicine, so companies
        hire the clinical people years before they learn the data needs
        protocols too: security, retention, what to do when something
        leaks. Sooner or later, somebody checks. The work here begins
        with the data instead of the paperwork, so when the
        questionnaire arrives, the right answers already exist.
      </p>
    </div>

    {/* the release valve — the ledger's obvious next question, answered
        with a door instead of two more sections of scrolling */}
    <p class="valve">
      <a class="valve-cue mono" href="#services">sound familiar? don’t want it to? → what we handle ↘</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .manifesto {
    /* the one violet room in the green house — the altered-state argument
       gets the altered surface; same luminance band as --void-deep */
    background: oklch(0.235 0.075 300);
    padding-block: var(--space-section);
  }

  /* scroll target only — the ring belongs on controls, not sections */
  .manifesto:focus-visible { outline: none; }

  .statement {
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    max-width: 16ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .dot {
    color: var(--acid);
    display: inline-block; /* scale needs a box */
  }
  .statement.draw.in .dot {
    animation: dot-pop 1.8s var(--ease-expo) 0.7s backwards;
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .statement.draw.in .dot { animation: none; }
  }

  .moments {
    list-style: none;
    margin: clamp(2.4rem, 5vh, 3.6rem) 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    max-width: 44rem;
    border-block-start: 1px solid var(--ink-faint);
  }

  .moments li {
    padding-block: clamp(0.8rem, 1.8vh, 1.2rem);
    border-block-end: 1px solid var(--ink-faint);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .body {
    max-width: 34em;
    margin-block-start: clamp(2.2rem, 5vh, 3.2rem);
  }
  .body p { margin: 0; }

  .valve { margin: 1.8rem 0 0; }

  .valve-cue {
    color: var(--acid);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-block;
    /* ≥44px target without moving the line */
    padding-block: 1em;
    margin-block: -1em;
  }
  .valve-cue:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
